  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Establishment of One Stop Gender-Based Violence (GBV) Centres in Mayukwayukwa and Maheba Local Integration Sites</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In order to improve the lives and rights of former refugees living in Zambia, IOM aims at preventing and responding to gender-based violence (GBV). In particular, IOM contributes to a reduction in GBV prevalence through strengthening of coordinated service provision for GBV survivorsusing the One Stop Centre (OSC) model. To that end, the project will support the refurbishment and establishment of two OSCs in Meheba and Mayukwayukwa resettlement areas, procure equipment and supplies for the same and conduct capacity building for the service providers in these sites.</narrative>
  </description>
